13 Section 1. Section 7-14-4501, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "7-14-4501. Acquisition, construction, and maintenance of parking areas. (1) A city or town
15 council may:
16 (1)(a) acquire by lease, gift, purchase, or condemnation pursuant to Title 70, chapter 30, lots or lands
17 for use as parking areas for motor vehicles;
18 (2)(b) construct and maintain on the acquired land or on any premises owned or under lease by the
19 city or town suitable parking facilities for the use of the public and for general traffic control; and
20 (3)(c) charge for the use of parking facilities.
21 (2) A city or town council that requires more parking spaces than those allowed in 76-2-304( 5 ) or
22 76-25-303(1)(i) for a new development shall compensate the property owner for the real cost of the construction
23 of the required parking. "
